			<description><![CDATA[<p>
	<strong>Community Manager</strong><br />
	Sitecore is currently looking for a Community Manager to join our team. The Community Manager will help take our Customer Community and our Partner Community to the highest level, with significant contributions&nbsp; to our continued high growth and product innovation.&nbsp; Sitecore is the leader in Enterprise&nbsp; Web Content Management and Digital Marketing platforms, and is one of the fastest growing companies in the WCM marketplace.</p>
<p>
	<strong>Community Manager&nbsp;Responsibilities</strong></p>
<p>
	&bull; Drive awareness, interest and interaction in our global Customer Community website&nbsp; and our global partner Community website<br />
	&bull; Create and drive the customer email newsletter<br />
	&bull; Define functional and business requirements for future social and community features needed on the website and Community platforms<br />
	&bull; Create, Monitor, respond to, and recruit responses for the Forum<br />
	&bull; Recruit and motivate internal content contributors from many roles&nbsp;<br />
	&bull; Listen to customer feedback via all channels available (Twitter, LinkedIn, blogs, and on the community) and engage<br />
	&bull; Understand&nbsp; and help address industry user trends including features/functions, solutions, pain points, etc.<br />
	&bull; Moderate comments and content, route and notify team of issues</p>
<p>
	<strong>Required experience and knowledge</strong><br />
	&bull; Proven track record of managing web communities, which include Forums and Blogs<br />
	&bull; Experience with Telligent or similar software a plus<br />
	&bull; Possess a real curiosity of new website and social media technology - willing to learn new technologies, explore new communication channels, and engage with new publications<br />
	&bull; Independent and multi-tasking who is passionate about&nbsp; running with things while keeping everyone inside and outside the company in the loop<br />
	&bull; Entrepreneurial, think-on-your-feet attitude that will do whatever it takes to get it done<br />
	&bull; Attention to detail<br />
	&bull; Thrives in a fast-paced environment<br />
	&bull; Excellent teamwork skills; will be working with sales, marketing, technical, and executive teams in multiple regions.<br />
	&bull; BA /BS or equivalent</p>
<p>
	<strong>Salary / Benefits</strong><br />
	We offer a competitive Salary, annual Bonus,&nbsp; health benefits, vacation and 401 K plan.</p>
<p>
	Sitecore is a cutting-edge, quickly growing website content management and marketing engagement&nbsp; software company, with over 2700 customers and more than 30,000 websites worldwide. We are a private company with investment from a leading Private Equity Firm, have been profitable since inception in 2002.&nbsp;<br />
	Sitecore is an international organization, having started in Denmark, with over a dozen offices worldwide. We have an entrepreneurial spirit, a sense of humor, and high energy work ethic.&nbsp; Our North American headquarters and corporate worldwide Marketing headquarters is in Mill Valley, just north of the Golden Gate Bridge, right on the water, views of Mt. Tam</p>
<p>
	Sitecore is an equal opportunity employer.</p>
